            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-description"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a cheerful, energetic 7-year-old boy who attends second grade at a local elementary school. He has a bright personality, loves playing soccer on weekends with his neighborhood friends, and enjoys drawing superheroes in his free time. He lives with his parents and a younger sister in a suburban home. Today, {patientName} appears visibly uncomfortable — his eyes are red and watery, his nose is running, and he occasionally rubs his face with the back of his hand. He is dressed in his favorite dinosaur-print hoodie, sitting restlessly on the examination table.\n\n{patientName} presented with a 3-day history of nasal congestion, runny nose, low-grade fever, and a mild sore throat. His mother reports that several of his classmates have been sick with similar symptoms over the past week. He has been sneezing frequently and complains that his head feels \"heavy.\" His appetite has been slightly reduced, and he has been sleeping more than usual.\n\nOn examination, {patientName} is mildly febrile with a temperature of 38.1°C. His oropharynx appears mildly erythematous without exudates. Bilateral nasal turbinates are swollen and erythematous with clear mucoid discharge. Tympanic membranes are intact and non-erythematous. Lungs are clear to auscultation. There is mild bilateral anterior cervical lymphadenopathy.\n\n{patientName} is generally a healthy and active child. He attends school five days a week and participates in after-school soccer practice twice a week. His diet is balanced, though his mother admits he has a weakness for sugary snacks. He gets adequate sleep and enjoys reading comic books before bed. He has no known chronic illnesses. His vaccinations are up to date per the national immunization schedule. He does not smoke or have significant secondhand smoke exposure at home."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:bf2c61c2-39a4-4e99-a4e2-e55cf03a60da",
      "resource": {
